pub.citation: Harrington, M. G. et al. 2005. Phylogenetic Inference in Sapindaceae Sensu Lato Using Plastid matK and rbcL DNA Sequences. Systematic Botany 30(2): 366-382.

pmmd.notes: Single most parsimonious tree of 1580 steps found from heuristic search of the combined rbcL and matK data. Support values, and other labeling as in Fig. 1; informative indels a and d-j are mapped on the tree. Anacardiaceae outgroup is a combination of rbcL sequence Buchanania latifolia and matK sequence Pleiogynium timorense.
